.TH "thermtrip_program" 9 "thermtrip_program" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
thermtrip_program \- Configures the hardware to shut down the system if a given sensor group reaches a given temperature
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" thermtrip_program
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "const struct tegra_tsensor_group *sg "  ","
.BI "int trip_temp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
ptr to the struct device for the SOC_THERM IP block
.IP "sg" 12
pointer to the sensor group to set the thermtrip temperature for
.IP "trip_temp" 12
the temperature in millicelsius to trigger the thermal trip at
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Sets the thermal trip threshold of the given sensor group to be the
\fItrip_temp\fP.  If this threshold is crossed, the hardware will shut
down.

Note that, although \fItrip_temp\fP is specified in millicelsius, the
hardware is programmed in degrees Celsius.
.SH "RETURN"
0 upon success, or -EINVAL upon failure.
